This function uses the `getline` function from the POSIX standard library to read a line of text from the file. The `getline` function returns the number of characters read, which is used to determine when to stop reading. The newline character at the end of the line is removed by setting the last character of the buffer to `\0`. The buffer is then returned. If an error occurs while reading, the function returns `NULL`.

